The paper discusses performance evaluation of Database Management Systems (DBMSs) in the context of data warehousing and On-Line Analytical Processing (OLAP). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the Data Warehouse Engineering Benchmark (DWEB), which is a tool for generating synthetic data warehouses and workloads. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the Extract, Transform, and Load (ETL) feature of DWEB, which is a common technique in Information Retrieval (IR) for preparing data for analysis. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of DWEB in Java, which is a programming language commonly used in Software Engineering (SE). This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
